The article announces several nominations and appointments for government positions. Brian S. Davis from North Carolina has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Defense (Manpower and Reserve Affairs). Currently, Davis serves as the Director of the Defense Personnel and Family Support Center for the Department of Defense. He has a background in aviation, having served as a pilot with Omega Air Refueling Services and commanding various Air Force units. Davis is a graduate of Campbell University and has received several awards for his service.

Alan Jackson from California has been nominated to be a Member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. Scott Dane from Minnesota has been nominated to be a Member of the President's Export Council.